entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how often do you go back to your hometown

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: never

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: why

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i do not like it there

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay how does it compare to la

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: oh it is completely boring and there is very little to do la is preferable i think to most places

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i see what you mean why did you move to la

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: because i was engaged to my fiancee and we lived in florida i moved there to be with him and he loves the water but i love the mountains and i missed hiking and i did not love florida and he was not tied to it so we decided we wanted to go somewhere we could both be happy and also have more opportunities in business and all of the great things that it has to offer

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good how easy was it for you to get used to living in la

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: very very easy

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are some things you really like about la

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: there is not much i do not like about la i love la i think it feels magical so many creative different people of all ages shapes sizes colors races the mountains the water the city all the things that there are to do all the people there are to meet i just i love everything about la

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay tell me about your relationship with your family

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i would rather not talk about that

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how easy is it for you to get a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: not very easy at all

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are you like when you do not sleep well

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: a lot better recently but i have a history of chronic insomnia and some health problems so it is challenging not to feel rested most of the time

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how have you been feeling lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: in the past week i have been feeling a lot better

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: can you tell me about that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes i the weather has changed spring has sprung it is a little warmer i was having more trouble with my depression in the winter and having trouble with tolerating cold and so i was not doing a lot of the things that i normally do and i also was sick with the flu and in the past week i decided that i was feeling better enough that i needed to kind of get out of my rut and start getting more focused around things things that i need to do during the day and walking my dog every day and not isolating so much and seeing some of my friends more so i was seeing i have been feeling a lot better like i have been making progress and that in the past week things have taken a more positive turn

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is great

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you been diagnosed with depression

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how long ago were you diagnosed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it is been quite some time officially it is probably been i do not know exactly but let is see maybe more than fifteen years ago

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what got you to seek help

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i was feeling suicidal

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you still go to therapy now

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: why did you stop

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: because i found a better alternative

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me more about that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i have been in therapy off and on since i was eighteen and i have tried a variety of methods and then i started working with a neurolinguistic prograer and that was really the first person that helped me make permanent changes and i was able to get off my anti depressants as well and even though i have struggled with some bouts of depression it is never been anything extremely severe and it was one of the best things that ever happened

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how did you decide to do that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well i was physically ill with chronic fatigue syndrome and i had a client that referred me to this person because he had cured her of that disease and that was he treats multiple issues and so everything is interrelated so once i had my first conversation with him i knew it was the right step for me

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how did you feel in that moment

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i was so happy i felt like i some i felt that i found the answer that i would been looking for that i had not given up hope and that i was on cloud nine that i i had been suffering for a a while a long time and i felt that i finally found the answer to the solution that i was looking for i was like it was the best thing i ever did in my life it was the best decision i ever made i felt extremely hopefuly for the first time in a long time

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is great tell me about something you did recently that you really enjoyed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i went to i went to a music store because i had been thinking about taking up an instrent i used to play the violin as a child and i have been wanting to do something that would give me more access to my creative side because i felt it is been extremely repressed and and so i went to the music store to try out to see what it would feel like to to handle an the instrent again nan and see if i thought that that was something i wanted to pursue

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: awesome

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it was awesome
